According to CONF-21043, the viewfile macro should be enforcing a 100,000 cell limit, after which it won't try to render the file.

The current (5.4.x) versions of Confluence does not seem to have limits on how many rows/columns/cells an Excel file can have and will happily attempt to render it in the viewfile macro. This can lead to out of memory errors.

This request is to explore the enforcement of upper limit on cells count that the viewfile macro will handle.

